e mainland. In the process, he sheds light on the complex relation between law and political culture in China. The book goes on to examine recent efforts in the People's Republic of China to develop intellectual property law, and uses this example to highlight the broader problems with China's program of law reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aAsian Studies. 4aLaw -- Intellectual Property and Technology. 7aLAW / Administrative Law & Regulatory Practice.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477929640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804779296423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804779296/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles